    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "13168a3b_a2e56c4b",
        "filename": "gce/api/config/v1/config.proto",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 69,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-02T02:34:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "given eventual migration of this to client repos, we\u0027d need to adopt some scheme for bot_id names to ensure that each client side config can be validated on its own. Suppose, we adopt a scheme \"\u003cproject\u003e/\u003cprefix\u003e\" for such configs.\n\nSo, can we ensure that some separator char (\"/\" in my example above) is reserved right now s.t. given a bot id we can always determine whether\n  * it\u0027s globally defined (ie infradata/config)\n  * it\u0027s project-specific (ie say fuchsia smth)\n\nAlternatively, maybe require client-side config from the start?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 67,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 69,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "ab1a0d60846d64beacbccec0b03a648270a50881",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f9ef2ae1_1008f4af",
        "filename": "gce/api/config/v1/config.proto",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 69,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-02T03:25:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "/ isn\u0027t a valid character in a GCE VM name. There\u0027s no good character to reserve because only a-zA-Z0-9- are allowed, meaning - is the only viable separator, and there are places where we already use -.\n\nI\u0027m not sure we\u0027re moving to client-side configs any time soon, I think we should revisit later.",
      "parentUuid": "13168a3b_a2e56c4b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 67,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 69,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "ab1a0d60846d64beacbccec0b03a648270a50881",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7273c9ea_00386bae",
        "filename": "gce/api/config/v1/config.proto",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 69,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-02T23:21:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I\u0027m not sure we\u0027re moving to client-side configs any time soon, I think we should revisit later.\n\nWe aren\u0027t only because nobody took initiative to do so. I\u0027m yet to hear someone objecting to doing this in general.\n\nSo, let\u0027s land this CL as is to unblock you. However, I think we should start discussion with luci-eng@ ASAP wrt to naming machines. We should have design ready before we start migrating to new MP (well, GCE backend).",
      "parentUuid": "f9ef2ae1_1008f4af",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 67,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 69,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "ab1a0d60846d64beacbccec0b03a648270a50881",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
