    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d90ddedc_9cba5c02",
        "filename": "gce/api/config/v1/kinds_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 50,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-02T02:34:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "suggestion (but not insistence) for config validation tests: I think having input specified is more concise and I\u0027d argue more useful for whose who try to read code/tests when actually error happens.\n\ntextpb :\u003d `\n  kind { name: \"dup\" }\n  kind { name: \"uniq\" }\n  kind { name: \"dup\" }\n`",
      "revId": "ab1a0d60846d64beacbccec0b03a648270a50881",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8dcbf29d_6067f36d",
        "filename": "gce/api/config/v1/kinds_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 50,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-02T03:25:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Makes testing indirect, because only the highest layer sees textproto. For example, if I add kind.Validate for each kind in kinds then I will only be able to test it by calling kinds.Validate on textproto, meaning kind.Validate tests now depend on kinds.Validate working correctly.",
      "parentUuid": "d90ddedc_9cba5c02",
      "revId": "ab1a0d60846d64beacbccec0b03a648270a50881",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4d1cfd6e_c4d2bed3",
        "filename": "gce/api/config/v1/kinds_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 50,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-02T23:21:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e  I will only be able to test it by calling kinds.Validate on textproto\n\nWell, firstly, I\u0027d argue that there is little value in testing individual Kind validation outside of kinds{} block.\nBut, if you see such value, you can still call validate on just a single Kind element of just unmarshaled kinds slice.\n\nanyways, this is just a suggestion. I don\u0027t feel strongly about this.",
      "parentUuid": "8dcbf29d_6067f36d",
      "revId": "ab1a0d60846d64beacbccec0b03a648270a50881",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "89ba9d82_6cd2ba92",
        "filename": "gce/api/config/v1/kinds_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 50,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-02T23:34:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The value is ease in reading/writing unit tests. If you change one unit, you only have to update the tests for that one unit. You shouldn\u0027t need to write correct textproto to test a function n levels removed from where textproto is even parsed.",
      "parentUuid": "4d1cfd6e_c4d2bed3",
      "revId": "ab1a0d60846d64beacbccec0b03a648270a50881",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
